speech.p:
9. In computing the tax payable by any holder of an office or employment of profit there may be deducted from the emoluments to be assessed:


(a)such expenses of travelling in the performance of the duties of the office of employment, or of keeping and maintaining a horse or other means of conveyance to enable him to perform the same, as he is necessarily obliged to incur and defray;

(b)any disbursements or expenses being money wholly and exclusively laid out or expended' for the purpose of such office or employment.
